< Review>
I had gone to Classy K-9 Clips for 10 years, but once she sold it to another owner, I thought I would try a new groomer.  What a mistake!  I have a long hair Chihuahua which my husband explained to the guy at the counter how we like the grooming to be done since it was his first visit.  When he picked him up he had shaved most of his coat to about 1/4 inch.  That has only happened once by mistake in the 13 years we have had him.  He looked like a cross between a poodle cut and a lion with a long mane.  They had shaved his pants off, but left puffs of hair on his legs.  We were not happy at all, but considering his age, we didn't think it would matter as much. We are on bonus time with his heart/kidney diseases.  After getting him home, we noticed they hadn't even cleaned his ears.  I don't know if it was an "off" day with the two guys working there, but we are never going again!< /Review>

< Review>
These arch supports saved the quality ofmy life. There were mornings I was unable to get out of bed because I was not able to stand on my feet. Literally, I would have to ease the burden of bearing my body weight unto my feet.  This almost daily ritual could take up to 40 minutes and even longer to fully stand some mornings. Often I would come home from work with my feet so sore that I would refuse to remove my shoes, because the security and tightness of the shoe was holding back pain.  I had frequent issues with my Achilles and often would have to refrain from excessive walking or running. Within a week of getting my supports, ALL of what I just described went away. 100%. I have zero issues with my feet now. My nagging back pain went away.  Who knew...? Had I known this was possible, I would have bought these several years earlier. Also, all my new shoes wear even on the soles, where as before I would have uneven premature wearing of corners and sides of the soles. It is not an exaggeration that these arch supports improved not only the quality of my life but my eagerness to do more activities. Places like amusement parks are enjoyable again... so far as the walking goes. This was an investment into quality of life and it is worth every penny.<//Review>

<user_name>Alex</user_name><date>1565781795152<//date>< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
One of the must see places near San Diego. Come either early in the morning or later in the day to avoid crowds and crazy traffic. Evenings are nicer as the sun comes down.

You‚Äôll be amazed by the cliffs, birds, and sea lions hanging out within just a few feet from people. Be mentally prepared for their smell, haha. Very entertaining and fun for all ages.

Overall, it‚Äôs a great place to witness wildlife and enjoy picturesque views of the ocean and cliffs. Sunset makes it even better!< /Review>

<userid>113947434597017087559< /userid><name>Chris Morris<//name><time>1541552971533<//time><Rating>4</Rating>< review>
There are lots of sea lions, seals, pelicans, and medium sized black birds here. The views are nice (cliffs overlooking the ocean). At the cove, itself, the animals are a bit far away, as they are down stairs sea level and you're up above (though you can kayak to them). Just down from the cove you can walk down to the water and get very close to the animals plus walk in the sand.< /review>

< text>
Really beautiful. A lot of wildlife. Fun place to go for lunch or dinner and then take a stroll and see all the sea lions and seals. Wear comfortable shoes if you plan on trying to get close to the sea lions and seals on the rocks etc so you don‚Äôt slip or fall. If you‚Äôre ever in San Diego this is definitely a place you have to check out.</text>

< review>
Wonderful place to take a romantic stroll, view a sunset and watch people get ridiculously close to wildlife. The area has been rebuilt over the past few years and is now super clean and very nice. Parking is still rough, so if you plan to see a sunset, get there about an hour before sundown.
Also...don't pet the sea lions.< /review>

< review>
Beautiful beach but the smell of the decomposing kelp is pretty off-putting and in some areas is unbearable. It would make La Jolla a perfect getaway if somehow that got cleared.

Sunset views were breathtaking.< /review>

< review>
Beautiful beach and cove, with tide pools, beautiful sea life, and sea shells. The views are gorgeous and there are lots of great spots to sit, relax and watch the tide come in. Very relaxing, natural atmosphere. Also, If you are a yogi or do meditation, this is a great place to do it. This is my go to beach whenever I come to San Diego.<//review>

< Review>
The menu is vast and varying, comprised of mostly rum-based drinks, but including a sprinkling of some based in other major spirits, as well. One of my favorite aspects is that each drink is shown with the silhouette of the glass it comes in (usually coupe, tallboy, or tumbler) next to it to help you picture what you'll get. Each drink we've had has been delicious, whether it's been sweet, smoky, strong, citrusy, or a complex combination of the above. I can't wait to return on my next trip to SF!< /Review>

<Text>Visiting from out of town and attending a birthday party there, someone associated with the birthday person brought two bottles of alcohol into the establishment as a gift. With approximately 15 folks, the birthday guy opened the bottles and poured a drink for several members. The bottles were rather small but each person who accepted received 1 glass and the bottles were emptied. The gift givers then left the establishment. Approximately 15 minutes later, one of the security staff had noticed one of the empty bottles and identified it as not being purchased at the clubs bar. He was visibly upset and called several other security staff over. The Birthday person explained the situation, apologized and instructed members of his party to purchase drinks from the bar. That obviously wasn't good enough for the staff. I (didn't have any drinks) asked the staff member proper policy and he stated "outside alcohol is not allowed here" I then asked "well how did it get past door security?" The security staff then went to get the black lady who was working the door to show her what had transpired as a result of her lack of proper protocol when allowing folks into the establishment. Instead of her admitting fault and just moving on, she started placing blame on everyone including myself (remember I didn't have any drinks nor did I know any of the folks involved other than the birthday guy). After her terrible acting job at being upset, the security staff huddled away and decided to ask us to all leave. Mind you, all the guys in our group were over 6 feet 200 lbs.. one of the females who had just arrived after the situation to this point asked why she was asked to leave and she was "manhandled" and jerked/led/pushed out of the club, I then realized that these staff were nothing more than unintelligent cowards at this point. I asked why I had to leave when I didn't consume any of the "prohibited alcohol" and they offered no excuse (nor did they bother to put their paws on me like they did the little lady). I kindly thanked the group for the invite and encouraged them to leave and they did so without further incident.  My advice to the club manager is to train your staff (especially the door staff) to not allow outside items into the establishment. If items such as outside bottles of alcohol as gifts are allowed in, place them behind the bar area (storage) and allow the receiver of the gift to retrieve when they leave for the evening... most importantly, admit fault when you are wrong... I was angry a bit and started to create club flyers and promote in areas like Compton and Watts, even sponsor transportation for "those folks" to attend the club possibly on a regular basis. Club LR staff I'm back in Texas and a bit disappointed that my last night in LA went like this, but it's all good now. If any of you are in Houston, look me up and I'll gladly show you some nice nightclubs when people use common sense, are not over dramatic and most importantly are able to handle situations as they come up accordingly.     Tim Hampton</Text>< pics>

<Date>1596556642643</Date>< rate>

<Text>If I could give a ZERO star, I would.

My complaint is that they are in the business of ripping people off.

I had ordered food from the taco truck next door (which by the way was horrible) and was told that they don't accept debit/credit card so I had to go to this store to get cash back. I went in the store and grabbed a small can of Pepsi and asked for $25 cash back. The total transaction was about $29 and I remember thinking, dang... I paid $4 for this small can of soda. Well, I just checked my bank account and it shows that I requested $27 cash back (I asked for $25 and got $25). I know it's only $2 but if they do this to every person that goes in there, that adds up. They gave me $25 and put $2 in their pockets.

Just Beware!</Text>< pictures>

< rate>

< Review>
ASN Depot is one of the best places to shop for a new computer, fit for any use. They have anything from home and work laptops, to gaming desktops and notebooks. Everything is custom made and built to perfection, and the durability of their products is unimaginable. <review>I wanted a high-end laptop to use while traveling and have had good luck with Dell products, both new and refurbished. ASN Depot had exactly what I wanted in a refurbished unit and offered some upgrade options. I contacted them several times with questions and their responses were always very prompt and courteous, even for dumb questions (I'd missed the answer in the description.)
When I got the laptop, it was perfect -- looked brand new and had exactly the upgrades I'd ordered. Except for one thing: I'd requested Windows 7 to be installed, and it came with Windows 8.1. An easy thing to overlook, as it had been early in our email chain when I had requested that.  This sort of thing has happened to me a number of times, and while not ideal, I can see how it could easily happen in our fast-paced society. As long as they make it right and time isn't an issue, I'm OK with it.
I contacted them and offered to install it myself if they'd send me the software. Understandably, they preferred to do it themselves to make sure it was done right, so paid for shipping both ways.
I got to thinking, I want to install Linux on this machine, maybe they'd be willing to make a couple of changes to make that process easier! And they did:
Guys, can you set up the BIOS to use legacy booting instead of UEFI? Sure, no problem.
How about repartitioning the boot drive to only use half of it for Windows 7, so I don't have to shrink the partition later? No problem.
How about turning off any fast boot options to avoid possible problems when shutting down Windows, booting Linux, making changes, then rebooting Windows? Done.
They called me when they were doing those changes to verify that they did exactly what I wanted, and they did. Exactly.
Excellent customer service, and always courteous. I'm a happy camper, the system is awesome, and I absolutely wouldn't hesitate to order from them again.<//review>< Pics>

A little confusing if you've never visited.  The young lady taking our order tartly asked if we knew what we wanted. Of course,  we had no idea how the ordering system worked.  I told her that I had looked over the menu and,  unless the edge of my steak would be expertly decorated in gold leaf, I think I'll just order water. Post disarmament, she laughed and was delightfully helpful =)

The steaks were impressive - juicy and cooked perfectly. The salad bar was fresh and more than adequate to complete a good steak dinner.

I ordered my steak medium, and the first time it came out rare. When I got our server‚Äôs attention I sent it back. It went back on the grill (after going onto the table and being cut into - MAJOR health code violation) and around 5-7 minutes later came out very well done. I sent it back a second time and they sent out a new steak. Cooked just as rare as the first one.

< review>
The quality of meat here has gone down a lot.

I ordered sirloin tips today for lunch.

Presentation was nice, two skewers loaded with meat, resting on a bed of rice. However after removing the wooden skewers there were at least half of the morsels of meat that consisted almost completely of gristle while the remaining pieces also were difficult to eat with slightly less strips of gristle and fat.

I brought this quietly to the attention of my server and she said everyone complains about it.

Is it just me or is something missing?

I saw a new feature upon arriving at the restaurant today, free valet parking! I did self park but am thinking money is being spent here in the wrong places by management.< /review>

<Text>I was under the impression that Sizzler had gone bankrupt in '89 and closed up shop everywhere soon after...until I moved back to CA and tasted truth for the first time in twenty years.

The ribs were dripping off the bone and melting in my mouth inbetween endless trips back and forth from the salad bar of wonder centerpieceing the restaurant.  The folks at Sizzler don't mind if you're feeding a party of three with only one 'AYCE'  salad bar purchase so don't feel bad that they do when you do.  This is Inglewood, right up the street from 'Randy's Doughnuts'  and 'Roscoes Chicken and Waffles' ; do you really think they care about how much salad you walk away with.
